OL,3,CParents threaten to leave island in
OL,4,Ccase of school closure
OL,6,FIn last week's States debate,
OL,7,FGuernsey's President of Education,
OL,8,FAndrea Dudley-Owen, stated that at the
OL,9,Fbeginning of the next school year,
OL,10,Fthere could be just one pupil at the
OL,11,Fschool which would cost #200,000 to
OL,12,Foperate.
OL,14,FHerm Island's leaseholder, John
OL,15,FSinger, disagrees.
OL,17,FHe expects to have four school pupils
OL,18,Fin Herm by September; there are eight
OL,19,Fpre-schoolers currently living there
OL,20,Fwho'll need to be educated in the next
OL,21,Fcouple of years.
